OL,3,CNorthern Ireland politicians react as
OL,4,CBurnham becomes Prime Minister
OL,6,FDUP leader Gavin Robinson said he
OL,7,Fwould welcome "early engagement" with
OL,8,FAndy Burnham as he started his
OL,9,Fpremiership on the "challenges"
OL,10,FNorthern Ireland is facing.
OL,12,FHe added: "A Prime Minister is always
OL,13,Fwelcome in Northern Ireland, I think
OL,14,Fit would be good to have early
OL,15,Fengagement with some of the challenges
OL,16,Fthat we face, not just around budgets
OL,17,Fand financial stability, but also
OL,18,Fpolitical stability, the interaction
OL,19,Fbetween Northern Ireland and the rest
OL,20,Fof the United Kingdom.
OL,26,@oD@OOUoD@`O]qD@TOUqD@_O]tD@KOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,418,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1784647107
OL,3,CNorthern Ireland politicians react as
OL,4,CBurnham becomes Prime Minister
OL,6,F"We know this Prime Minister has an
OL,7,Finterest in devolution, but he thinks
OL,8,Fabout that through the prism of
OL,9,Fdevolution within England, and there
OL,10,Fare clearly opportunities but
OL,11,Fchallenges associated with our
OL,12,Fdevolved settlement and discussions
OL,13,Fwill need to be had in that regard."
OL,15,FAlliance MP Sorcha Eastwood called on
OL,16,FAndy Burnham to urgently address
OL,17,Fissues facing Stormont - with no
OL,18,Fagreed budget, a projected Executive
OL,19,Foverspend of approximately #1.5bn, and
OL,20,Fgrowing calls for reform of the
OL,21,Finstitutions.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
